Diagnosis
. Scape completely dark (
Figs 59, 60
); legs (
Fig. 37
): femora dark and metallic with apical ¼–½ white; fore tibia with anterior surface white and posterior surface dark and metallic or dark brown, mid and hind tibiae dark and metallic with apical 
¼
–¼ white, males frequently with median part of tibiae pale (
Fig. 78
), but males with tibiae predominantly dark, as in females, also occur; fore wing speculum with dense setation (
Fig. 73
); pronotum and mesoscutum with white setae; scutellum green to golden (
Figs 9, 10
), occasionally reddish; male gaster completely dark (
Fig. 10
).
